 somebody else originated the\nname of \u201cFrank\u201d and tacked it on\nto the last, which made the name\nread \"Frank Montgomery.\"\n\u201cMr. Montgomery\" one day awoke\nto the fact that entirely through ac\ncident he had firmly established him\nself in business and was becoming\nwidely known under a name not his\nown! That thought startled him, and\nfor some time he is said to have con\nsidered taking back his original name\nof \"William Russell Bevit.\u201d And\nthen he remembered ha would loee\nnearly all the advertising value that\nlay in the good-natured, rollicking\n\"Monty.\u201d\nF ..rn..a.m T .1 I. T L*. AW\u2014 H\nThe Washington Times\nCOMBINATION\nCLASSIFIED\nADVERTISING RATES\nFOB\nTHE MORNING HERALD\nAND\nTHE EVENING TIMES\nAt the following rates advertisers are\nnermitted to use both The Morning\nHerald and The Bvening Times. 2 papers\nfor one price.\n20c per Agate Lino (Sunday)\n24c per Agate Line 1 day\n21c per Agate Lino, per day 2 days\nISe per Agate Line, per day 1 days\nMinimum co\u00bbt, ahy Advertisement.\nTwo Lines.\nTELEPHONE YOUR WANTS TO\nMAIN 8200.\nTHE\nWASHINGTON HERALD 1\nDAILY AND SUNDAY\nRate delivered by carrier In Washing\nton and Alexandria. The Waahington\nHERALD Daily and Sunday, is delivered\nby carriers at 20c per week; dally only.\n10c per week; Sunday only, 10c per\nwedk. Orders can be sent by mail or\ntelephone Main 8280. Collection is mads\nweakly by carriers. _ _ _\nSPECIAL COMBINATION RATE\nDaily and Sunday HERALD and\nEvening TIMKS.\n20c per week. Delivered by Carrier.\n13 edttldhe for 20c.\nRATE BY MAIL\nPAYABLE IN ADVANCE.\nDAILY AND SUNDAY.\nOne Tear 310.00\nSix Months 8.00\nThree Month/ 2.80\nOne Month T 88\nDAILY ONLY. SUNDAY ONLY.\nOne Year 88.00 Ono Year *6.00\nSix Months... 2.80 Six Months... 8.60\nThree Monthe. 1.26 Three Months. 1.36\nOne Month .50 One Month... .48\nDeath Notice*\nTRAMMELL\u2014 Monday, Sept. 3, 1323, at\n0 p. m.. at her residence. Idylwood.\nVa., GRACE AGNES, beloved wife of\nSidney Maur